@server = http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/service-desk

### Erin (requester) — should see only her own tickets
GET {{server}}/Operations
Authorization: Basic erin:
### As erin, try to update a ticket she owns
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/service-desk/Operations(ID=d0000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000003,IsActiveEntity=true)
Authorization: Basic erin:

GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/service-desk/Comments
Authorization: Basic erin:


### Aiden (agent) — should see the whole queue
GET {{server}}/Operations
Authorization: Basic aiden:

### Admin — should see everything
GET {{server}}/Operations
Authorization: Basic admin:

### A code list — any logged-in user can read
GET {{server}}/Statuses
Authorization: Basic erin:

### Create a ticket as Erin
POST {{server}}/Operations
Authorization: Basic erin:
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Printer not working",
  "description": "Paper jam on floor 3",
  "urgency_code": "HIGH"
}
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/service-desk/Configuration
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/service-desk/$metadata



{ "text": "Any update on this?" }